+++ About
Here at SCPD, we believe practically **anything** can be an SCP. We have SCPs about everything from [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/SCP-297 a vibrator that disintegrates anything on contact] to [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/SCP-3006 We Are Number One] to [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/SCP-1247 Actual Cannibal Shia LaBeouf]. So, we've decided to push that to its limits!

The basis for this contest is going to be heavily inspired by [*https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/cliche-con-2019 Cliché-Con 2019]. As with Cliché-Con, consider this a challenge. Can you take the weirdest, most bizarre parts of our internet culture and turn them into a real SCP? I bet you can!

//So, what is a meme, you may ask?// This should be fairly self-explanatory but memes have existed on the internet practically [*https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/original/000/328/405/f29.gif since its inception.] Internet Memes tend to be culturally pervasive images, ideas, stories, fragments that get passed around almost like a virus, changing meaning and mutating beyond its original intent. //Generally,// they are meant to be humorous but that is not always the case. 

For this contest, use your best judgement, and if you really are unsure, feel free to message [[*user Woedenaz]]

Additionally, keep [*https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/ CC BY-SA 3.0] in mind as not all memes are okay under this license. //Writing// about them is likely acceptable but using an image of them might not be. If unsure, it is best to ask the SCP Licensing team and/or contact [[*user Elenee FishTruck]].

------

[[div_ class="blockquote"]]
+++ Contest Rules
[[ol_]]
[[li]]Your SCP //must// have //at least// one meme as its basis (yes, you can have more than one.) It must be featured prominently in the article. If you are unsure, message [[*user Woedenaz]] either via PM or Discord.[[/li]]
[[li]]A memetic-based SCP does **not** count as a meme-based SCP. The SCP can, of course, be memetic in nature but that, alone, does not count.[[/li]]
[[li]]Your article must be a main-list SCP, not a tale. This also means it cannot be a -J or -EX.[[/li]]
[[li]]You are allowed to make minor edits after the posting period is over, ie. minor formatting, grammar and spelling mistakes, anything that does not change the bulk of the article.[[/li]]
[[li]]Your article must be at least +20 to be considered for the prizes.[[/li]]
[[li]]The article must be newly written and not based on something previously written or sitting in your sandbox. [[/li]]
[[li]]After posting the article, make an author post explaining what the meme you used is (even if it is obvious within the article.)[[/li]]
[[li]]Only ONE article is allowed for entry.[[/li]]
[[li]]Collaboration is allowed in teams of a maximum of TWO. If you collaborate, that counts as both collaborator's ONE article.[[/li]]
[[li]]Act in //good faith.// Do not take unusual or extraordinary actions to spur on votes for your's or any competitor's article. This includes:[[/li]]
[[ul_]]
[[li]]Mass PMing users on **any** platform asking for your article to be read or voted on.[[/li]]
[[li]]Using your platform as an "influencer" to funnel your fans towards your article.[[/li]]
[[li]]Downvoting all competitor's articles or trying to encourage others to downvote competitor's articles.[[/li]] 
[[/ul]]
[[/ol]]
